    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI think 767fbd88ff broke completion auto-trigger based on trigger characters, where after typing them (which triggers completion and eventual popup menu, are removed on completion selection.\n\nChecking out a562fb33ca makes the issue disappear.\n\n**Only tested with `clangd` as the only LSP I use**.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nEnable LSP completion with autotrigger enabled:\n```lua\n              vim.lsp.completion.enable(true, client.id, args.buf, { autotrigger = true })\n```\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/64e0d08c-880a-4cb0-813f-cb9feeabfa8b\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTrigger characters preserved.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-532+g84d5c5f4bf Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1774896198\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 22.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n.\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\n.\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
