        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "BTW, in trying to debug the issue, I factored out the new logic into a separate function:\n\n```diff\ndiff --git a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua b/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua\nindex 4f6c9022ea..b3c6c05111 100644\n--- a/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua\n+++ b/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua\n@@ -168,6 +168,21 @@ local function apply_snippet(item)\n   end\n end\n \n+\n+--- Fallback function.\n+---\n+--- @param text string\n+--- @param word string\n+--- @param prefix string\n+--- @param match fun(text: string, prefix: string):boolean\n+--- @return string\n+local function get_completion_word_fallback(text, word, prefix, match)\n+  if text and not match(word, prefix) then\n+    return text\n+  end\n+  return word\n+end\n+\n --- Returns text that should be inserted when a selecting completion item. The\n --- precedence is as follows: textEdit.newText > insertText > label\n ---\n@@ -212,15 +227,9 @@ local function get_completion_word(item, prefix, match)\n     local word = item.textEdit.newText\n     word = string.gsub(word, '\\r\\n?', '\\n')\n     word = word:match('([^\\n]*)') or word\n-    if item.filterText and not match(word, prefix) then\n-      return item.filterText\n-    end\n-    return word\n+    return get_completion_word_fallback(item.filterText, word, prefix, match)\n   elseif item.insertText and item.insertText ~= '' then\n-    if item.filterText and not match(item.insertText, prefix) then\n-      return item.filterText\n-    end\n-    return item.insertText\n+    return get_completion_word_fallback(item.filterText, item.insertText, prefix, match)\n   end\n   return item.label\n end\n```\n\nJust as a marker, to avoid code duplication as much as possible.",
